  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 7098.9 sitting between the max negative gamma at 7115 (-4374M) and positive gamma wall at 7100 (+4919M), dealers are likely buying this dip aggressively as they're short gamma below the flip at 6872 in this localized pocket. The PIN regime suggests mean reversion behavior, but the \"wall_break\" event indicates we've likely breached the 7100 support level, forcing dealers to buy into weakness while the massive 7200 gamma wall (+7442M) should act as strong resistance on any bounce. Key levels to watch are the 7100 reclaim for stabilization and 7115 where dealer buying pressure intensifies, with upside capped by the 7150-7200 gamma wall complex.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect dealers to buy the dip here with upside limited to the 7150-7200 zone.",
